public class Path
extends java.util.LinkedList<ActionStatePair>

This class models a path that traces the route from a root node to a node in the tree. Basically it is a list of ActionStatePair objects plus a head node (of State). Conceptually a path is a specialised list of action-state pairs with a head node. That is why it is extending a concrete class implementing the List interface. I chose LinkedList in this case. It can be any class that implements List. You do not have much to do with this class. A Path is return as the result when you do a search. If it is not null, you can simply call the print() method to print out the path.

Author:
Kit-ying Hui
